name: Al Jazeera World
content: A devastating earthquake hit Morocco's Atlas Mountains on September 8, resulting in the loss of nearly 3,000 lives and affecting communities already suffering poverty and neglect. Al Jazeera World's film "Morocco’s Village Superwomen" tells the story of the women in Oum-er-Rbia and Tiglit villages in the Atlas who run households while their husbands work in other cities. Their villages were unaffected by the recent quake.Watch the film: https://aje.me/atlas
